First, we claim that the map        \begin {aligned}       \Phi  \colon  \hat {C}(yA, F) &\to  FA\\             \alpha  &\mapsto  \alpha _A(1_A)       \end {aligned}     
    is a bijection. The inverse        \Psi  \colon  FA \to  \hat {C}(yA, F)     sends any x\in  FA to the natural transformation with components        \Psi  x_B: C(B,A)\to  FB,\quad  f\mapsto  Ff(x).     
    Naturality of \Psi  x entails, for any B\xleftarrow {f} B'\in  C^\text {op}, commutativity of 




