    To show these are inverses, first let x\in  FA; now        \Psi (\Phi (x)) = \Phi  x_A (1_A) = F1_A (a) = a.     
    Next, let yA \xrightarrow {\alpha } F; we want to show that        \alpha  = \Phi (\Psi (\alpha )).      We will do this by showing the components agree. Again letting
    A\xleftarrow {f} B, naturality of \alpha  asserts that 




